
// This Hyperlambda code checks if the [stream] argument is either explicitly set to false or does not exist at all. The [or] slot evaluates to true if either of its conditions is true: the [eq] slot checks if [stream] equals false, and the [not-exists] slot checks if [stream] is absent.
or
   eq:x:@.arguments/*/stream
      .:bool:false
   not-exists:x:@.arguments/*/stream
